                        <p style="font-size:1.2em; margin:0;"><strong>Step 2:</strong> Choose an encoding (ASCII, UTF-8, UTF-16, UTF-32).</p>
                        <p class="small-text">UTF-8 is variable length (1–4 bytes); ASCII is 1 byte.</p>
                    </div>
                </section>
                <section>
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom:1rem;">How Does Text Become Bits?</h3>
                    <div class="question-box">
                        <p style="font-size:1.2em; margin:0;"><strong>Step 3:</strong> Store the binary pattern for each code point.</p>
                        <p class="small-text">Example: 'A' in ASCII → 01000001.</p>
